---
import SiteLayout from '../layouts/SiteLayout.astro';
import Waitlist from '../components/Waitlist.astro';
---

<SiteLayout
  title="Deckyard — Slides that stay on brand. Coming soon."
  description="Deckyard is an upcoming open source presentation platform for European nonprofits, public institutions and cultural organizations. On brand by default, built for humans and AI agents, hosted on your terms. Coming soon."
>
  <!-- ============ HERO ============ -->
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container hero-inner">
      <p class="kicker kicker--center" data-reveal>Coming soon · Open source · Made in Europe</p>
      <h1 data-reveal data-reveal-delay="80">
        Slides that stay on brand.<br />
        <span class="accent">Data that stays yours.</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="lead" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="160">
        Deckyard is an open source presentation platform for nonprofits, public institutions
        and cultural organizations in Europe. Every deck your team makes looks like it came
        from your design department, lives on infrastructure you control, and can be built
        by humans and AI agents alike.
      </p>
      <div data-reveal data-reveal-delay="240">
        <Waitlist id="hero" />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ============ WHAT SHIPS ============ -->
  <section class="section section-tint">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-head section-head--center" data-reveal>
        <p class="kicker kicker--center">Under the hood</p>
        <h2>Coming soon, but already built</h2>
        <p class="lead">
          This isn't a waitlist for an idea. Deckyard is a working platform in daily use;
          we're polishing the edges before the source goes public. Here's what ships.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="pillars pillars--features">
        <div class="pillar" data-reveal>
          <div class="pillar-icon" aria-hidden="true">
            <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><rect x="3" y="3" width="7" height="7" rx="1.5"/><rect x="14" y="3" width="7" height="7" rx="1.5"/><rect x="3" y="14" width="7" height="7" rx="1.5"/><rect x="14" y="14" width="7" height="7" rx="1.5"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3>35+ slide types</h3>
          <p>
            Charts, timelines, matrices, funnels, KPIs, galleries, quotes and more:
            structured layouts that do the design, so your team only types content.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="pillar" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="60">
          <div class="pillar-icon" aria-hidden="true">
            <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M12 3v2M12 19v2M3 12h2M19 12h2M5.6 5.6l1.4 1.4M17 17l1.4 1.4M5.6 18.4 7 17M17 7l1.4-1.4"/><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="4"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3>Built for AI agents</h3>
          <p>
            A full MCP server with 20+ tools. Point Claude or Cursor at your workspace and
            it drafts, restructures and refines entire decks, always in your theme.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="pillar" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="120">
          <div class="pillar-icon" aria-hidden="true">
            <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M16 21v-2a4 4 0 0 0-4-4H6a4 4 0 0 0-4 4v2"/><circle cx="9" cy="7" r="4"/><path d="M22 21v-2a4 4 0 0 0-3-3.87M16 3.13a4 4 0 0 1 0 7.75"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3>Real collaboration</h3>
          <p>
            Invite collaborators with granular permissions, comment on slides in real time,
            edit together without conflicts, and roll back with version history.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="pillar" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="180">
          <div class="pillar-icon" aria-hidden="true">
            <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="9"/><path d="M3 12h18M12 3c2.5 2.6 3.9 5.7 3.9 9S14.5 18.4 12 21c-2.5-2.6-3.9-5.7-3.9-9S9.5 5.6 12 3Z"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3>Publish anywhere</h3>
          <p>
            Put a deck on the web in one click, share it with a link, or embed it in your
            own site with the JS SDK. Social preview images come free.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="pillar" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="240">
          <div class="pillar-icon" aria-hidden="true">
            <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M3 11h4l3 8 4-16 3 8h4"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3>Live audiences</h3>
          <p>
            Polls, Likert scales, moderated Q&amp;A, feedback and lead capture on the slides
            themselves; per-slide analytics tell you afterwards what landed.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="pillar" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="300">
          <div class="pillar-icon" aria-hidden="true">
            <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><circle cx="13.5" cy="6.5" r="1"/><circle cx="17.5" cy="10.5" r="1"/><circle cx="8.5" cy="7.5" r="1"/><circle cx="6.5" cy="12.5" r="1"/><path d="M12 2C6.5 2 2 6.5 2 12s4.5 10 10 10c.9 0 1.8-.7 1.8-1.7 0-.4-.2-.8-.4-1.1-.3-.3-.4-.7-.4-1.1 0-.9.7-1.7 1.7-1.7H17c2.8 0 5-2.2 5-5C22 6 17.5 2 12 2Z"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3>Your brand as software</h3>
          <p>
            Fonts, colors, logos and layout rules defined once as a theme. Everyone is on
            brand automatically; rebrand centrally and every deck follows.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="pillar" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="360">
          <div class="pillar-icon" aria-hidden="true">
            <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M21 15v4a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H5a2 2 0 0 1-2-2v-4M7 10l5 5 5-5M12 15V3"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3>No lock-in</h3>
          <p>
            Export to PDF, PowerPoint, self-contained HTML, PNG or JSON at any time. Your
            decks are documents you own, never records in someone else's cloud.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="pillar" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="420">
          <div class="pillar-icon" aria-hidden="true">
            <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><rect x="2" y="3" width="20" height="7" rx="2"/><rect x="2" y="14" width="20" height="7" rx="2"/><path d="M6 6.5h.01M6 17.5h.01"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3>Self-host in an afternoon</h3>
          <p>
            One Docker Compose file, Node and Postgres. Run it on your own servers under
            your own rules, or wait for our hosted version on European infrastructure.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ============ OPEN SOURCE RELEASE + CTA ============ -->
  <section class="section section-dark">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-head" data-reveal>
        <p class="kicker">Open source, opening soon</p>
        <h2>Be there when the gates open</h2>
        <p class="lead">
          Deckyard is MIT licensed, GDPR native and built to be self-hosted. The repository
          goes public once the docs and onboarding are worthy of it. Leave your address and
          you'll hear the moment it does.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div data-reveal data-reveal-delay="120">
        <Waitlist id="footer" buttonLabel="Join the waitlist" />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</SiteLayout>
